org.opends.server.replication.server

Class ExpectedAcksInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opends.server.replication.server.ExpectedAcksInfo
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SafeDataExpectedAcksInfo, SafeReadExpectedAcksInfo

    public abstract class ExpectedAcksInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the mother class for sub-classes holding any information needed about the acks that the replication server will wait for, when he receives an update message with the assured flag on (assured replication acknowledgments expected). It also includes info/routines for constructing the final ack to be sent to the sender of the update message. It is expected to have one sub-class per assured replication sub mode.

      • changeNumber

        protected ChangeNumber changeNumber
        The change number of the assured update message we want acks for.

      • expectedServersAckStatus

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Boolean> expectedServersAckStatus
        This gives the list of servers we are willing to wait acks from and the information about the ack from the servers. key: the id of the server. value: a boolean true if we received the ack from the server, false otherwise.

      • serversInTimeout

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> serversInTimeout
        Facility for monitoring: If the timeout occurs for the original update, we call createAck(true) in the timeout code for sending back an error ack to the original server. We use this call to also save the list of server ids for server we did not have time to receive an ack from. For updating its counters, the timeout code can then call getTimeoutServers() method to now which servers did not respond in time.
